{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
In [[general relativity]], the '''topogravitic tensor''' is one of the three pieces of the [[Bel decomposition]] of the [[Riemann tensor]].

The topogravitic tensor can be interpreted as representing the [[sectional curvature]]s for the spatial part of a [[frame fields in general relativity|frame field]].

